    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A wealthy merchant class of people, particularly those living in Kyoto, who became major patrons of art in Japan during the Momoyama (1573-1615) and Edo (1615-1868) periods and thus influenced the production of painting styles from the 16th to 19th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
